 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>&#8212;Mary Oliver</em></p></blockquote><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">Aside from the doomers who believe that AI will kill us all and =
the techno-utopians who believe it will solve all of our problems, there ar=
e three main ways that people seem to be thinking about AI.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">At one extreme, you might fear that AI will take your job. Cert=
ainly, you&#8217;ve read as much in the press, and it does seem to be getti=
ng better and better at the things you&#8217;re paid to do. On this extreme=
, AI is scary.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In the middle, you might feel AI =
FOMO, feel that you need to &#8220;learn AI&#8221; or &#8220;leverage AI&#8=
221; because everyone else is doing it and you don&#8217;t want to miss out=
=2E From this position, AI is overwhelm=
ing: how can you ever keep up?&#160;</=
p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;">A third, far more productive approach is to first deter=
mine what you uniquely want to accomplish with your life, and then view eve=
rything, including AI, through the lens of whether it helps you accomplish =
your goal. From this perspective, AI is a tool and you are the one who wiel=
ds.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You can wait for the Sandworm to swallow you=
 whole or set a thumper, grab your hooks, and ride it.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;"><span>Would a practically free army of near-genius employees help yo=
u accomplish the one thing you want to accomplish? Is GPT-4 or Claude 3 or =
Gemini 1.5 Pro or Mistral Lage better at what you need it to do? Or is each=
 better at one particular thing you need them to do? Oh! Look, this new mod=
el just dropped and it seems like it solves </span><em>exactly </em><span>t=
he thing I&#8217;m looking to solve. I&#8217;ll hire that one, too.&#160;</=
span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s more than just AI, though. We are luc=
ky enough to be alive in the most incredible time in human history. Beyond =
AI, people are making rapid progress across a number of fields at the same =
time: space, manufacturing, robotics, energy, bio, crypto.&#160;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">All that progress can be overwhelming or empowering, and which o=
f those two it is is entirely up to you.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64=
, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>I=
&#8217;m here to tell you: </span><strong>you can simply decide to do big t=
hings.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And I&#8217;m=
 here to argue that </span><strong>you should spend the time to figure out =
the most ambitious thing you could dream of doing with your one wild and pr=
ecious life.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When you name your ambitio=
n, it seems that the world conspires to help you achieve it, because you be=
come more aware of all the tools at your disposal.&#160;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">In naming your ambition, name something big, something you can uniquely =
achieve.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You&#8217;re lucky enough to be alive at a ti=
me when the world is building new, more powerful tools to help you achieve =
your goal at a faster clip than it ever has.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rg=
b(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Let=
 me get more specific, with something small that I have experienced so many=
 times that I know it to be true.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I read in two =
modes: aimlessly or with a goal.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When I&#8217;m =
reading aimlessly, I simply enjoy the words and the stories. Maybe I learn =
something that influences my thinking, or gives me an idea for an essay, or=
 tucks away into my subconscious to surface when the time is right. But it&=
#8217;s a form of entertainment. It&#8217;s a passive thing.&#160;</p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">Reading with a goal is a different experience altogether. When=
