you on your quest. There&#8217;s a simple reason for that, too.&#160;</span=
></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Ambition is like mass. The more you have, th=
e stronger your gravitational pull.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Read any account of working at SpaceX or talk to anyone who&#8217=
;s worked there. It sounds brutally hard. And yet, SpaceX is one of the mos=
t highly sought after employers in the world, in large part because of Elon=
&#8217;s ambition to take humans off this world. Only one group of people w=
ill be the first to make humans multiplanetary.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
Those who met him still speak of Steve Jobs&#8217; reality distortion field=
, nearly thirteen years after his death. His ambition warped the fabric of =
reality around his goals.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Satoshi Nakamoto=
